Exercise: Ice Cream Flavor Voting Booth
Create a program that simulates an ice cream flavor voting booth where users can vote for their favorite ice cream flavors. The program will tally the votes and determine the most popular flavor based on the votes received.

Instructions:
1. Define an ArrayList to store the different ice cream flavors available for voting.
2. Prompt users to vote for their favorite ice cream flavor. Allow users to input their votes as strings representing the ice cream flavors.
3. Use a loop to iterate through the votes and tally the number of votes received for each ice cream flavor using the accumulator pattern.
4. Determine the most popular ice cream flavor by finding the flavor with the highest number of votes.
5. Display the results, including the total number of votes for each flavor and the most popular flavor chosen by users.

Sample Code (simplified version):

```java
import java.util.ArrayList;
import java.util.HashMap;
import java.util.Map;
import java.util.Scanner;

public class IceCreamVotingBooth {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ArrayList<String> flavors = new ArrayList<>();
        flavors.add("Vanilla");
        flavors.add("Chocolate");
        flavors.add("Strawberry");
        flavors.add("Mint Chocolate Chip");

        Map<String, Integer> votes = new HashMap<>();
        Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);

        System.out.println("Welcome to the Ice Cream Flavor Voting Booth!");

        for (String flavor : flavors) {
            votes.put(flavor, 0);
        }

        System.out.print("Enter the number of voters: ");
        int numVoters = scanner.nextInt();
        scanner.nextLine(); // Consume newline

        for (int i = 0; i < numVoters; i++) {
            System.out.print("Voter " + (i + 1) + ", please enter your favorite ice cream flavor: ");
            String vote = scanner.nextLine();

            if (flavors.contains(vote)) {
                votes.put(vote, votes.get(vote) + 1);
                System.out.println("Thank you for voting!");
            } else {
                System.out.println("Invalid flavor! Please select a valid flavor.");
            }
        }

        int totalVotes = votes.values().stream().mapToInt(Integer::intValue).sum();
        String mostPopularFlavor = flavors.get(0);

        for (String flavor : flavors) {
            if (votes.get(flavor) > votes.get(mostPopularFlavor)) {
                mostPopularFlavor = flavor;
            }
            System.out.println(flavor + ": " + votes.get(flavor) + " votes");
        }

        System.out.println("Total votes: " + totalVotes);
        System.out.println("The most popular ice cream flavor is: " + mostPopularFlavor);

        scanner.close();
    }
}
```

In this Ice Cream Flavor Voting Booth exercise, users can vote for their favorite ice cream flavors, and the program tallies the votes to determine the most popular flavor chosen by users. This light-hearted exercise adds a fun twist to practicing ArrayList, loops, finding elements, and the accumulator pattern in Java programming. Enjoy the sweet and amusing voting experience!

