Exercise: Ice Cream Order Management
Create a program that simulates an ice cream shop's order management system using ArrayLists. The program will allow users to place ice cream orders, customize their orders with toppings and flavors, and display the order details.

Instructions:
1. Define multiple ArrayLists to store ice cream flavors, toppings, and customer orders.
2. Populate the ArrayLists with available ice cream flavors and toppings for customers to choose from.
3. Enable users to place custom ice cream orders by selecting flavors and toppings. Each order should be represented as a combination of flavors and toppings stored in an ArrayList.
4. Implement functionalities to add, modify, and remove items from the order based on user input.
5. Display the customer's final ice cream order, including selected flavors and toppings.

Sample Code (simplified version):

```java
import java.util.ArrayList;
import java.util.Scanner;

public class IceCreamOrderManagement {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ArrayList<String> availableFlavors = new ArrayList<>();
        availableFlavors.add("Vanilla");
        availableFlavors.add("Chocolate");
        availableFlavors.add("Strawberry");
        availableFlavors.add("Mint Chocolate Chip");

        ArrayList<String> availableToppings = new ArrayList<>();
        availableToppings.add("Sprinkles");
        availableToppings.add("Chocolate chips");
        availableToppings.add("Whipped cream");
        availableToppings.add("Caramel sauce");

        ArrayList<String> order = new ArrayList<>();
        Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);

        System.out.println("Welcome to the Ice Cream Order Management System!");

        System.out.println("Available Flavors:");
        for (String flavor : availableFlavors) {
            System.out.println(flavor);
        }

        System.out.println("Available Toppings:");
        for (String topping : availableToppings) {
            System.out.println(topping);
        }

        System.out.println("Please select an ice cream flavor:");
        String flavor = scanner.nextLine();
        order.add(flavor);

        System.out.println("Please select additional toppings (separate each topping with a comma):");
        String[] toppings = scanner.nextLine().split(",");
        for (String topping : toppings) {
            order.add(topping.trim());
        }

        System.out.println("Your Ice Cream Order:");
        for (String item : order) {
            System.out.println(item);
        }

        scanner.close();
    }
}
```

In this Ice Cream Order Management exercise, users can select ice cream flavors and toppings to create custom orders using ArrayLists. By interacting with the program, users can place and customize their ice cream orders, reinforcing ArrayList usage in a fun and interactive context within a creative ice cream shop scenario. Enjoy building and customizing delicious ice cream orders with this simple and engaging exercise!
